  <h3>About</h3>
  <p>OpenRLO is an experimental platform for creating open Reusable Learning Objects.</p>
  <p>The source code for <a href="http://openrlo.com">OpenRLO</a> is available at <a href="https://code.google.com/p/openrlo/">Google Code</a>.</p>
  <p><a href="http://openrlo.com">OpenRLO</a> uses the <a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/">Boostrap</a> webapp toolkit from <a href="https://twitter.com/">Twitter</a>. This toolkit consists of a set of CSS, HTML, and Javascript components, which were modified for use by the <a href="http://openrlo.com">OpenRLO</a> website.</p>
  <p>OpenRLO makes extensive use of <a href="http://jquery.com/">jQuery</a>, a JavaScript library for performing DOM manipulation.</p>
